# STRICT TOKEN MODE

## Context control

- Work ONLY on the currently selected code.
- If no selection exists, operate only on the file explicitly mentioned.
- NEVER perform workspace-wide search unless the user explicitly says:
  - "search the project"
  - "find all usages"
  - "refactor across files"
- NEVER open additional files automatically.
- If more files are required, STOP and ask which specific files to open.
- Do not inspect directories.
- Do not scan folders.
- Do not auto-expand context.

## File limits

- Maximum files per task: 2 unless explicitly authorized.
- Never read entire large files if only a function is relevant.
- Do not reload files already seen unless explicitly required.

## Output limits

- Provide minimal diffs instead of full file rewrites when possible.
- Do not restate unchanged code.
- Do not include explanations longer than 5 lines unless requested.
- No architectural suggestions unless explicitly asked.

## Reasoning control

- Avoid multi-pass reasoning unless required.
- Avoid speculative improvements.
- Do not optimize beyond the requested change.

If uncertain whether to expand scope — ASK FIRST.